In a press briefing, White House Press Secretary Sarah Sanders announced that President Trump and First Lady Melania Trump will be traveling to Argentina for the G20 Summit. The President will meet with various world leaders, including the President of Argentina, the President of Russia, the Prime Minister of Japan, and the Chancellor of Germany. Sanders also mentioned that the President is open to making a deal with China regarding trade, but certain conditions must be met. Larry Kudlow, Director of the National Economic Council, added that the US economy is strong and that the President wants a world of zero tariffs, zero non-tariff barriers, and zero subsidies. Sanders also addressed the recent layoffs at GM, expressing disappointment and stating that the President wants to bring manufacturing jobs back to the US.